I'll calculate the Quick Ratio and Net Profit Margin based on the financial statements provided.

## Calculating the Quick Ratio

The Quick Ratio is calculated as:
Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities

From the balance sheet:
- Current Assets = $9,891,156.92
- Inventory = $343,000.00
- Current Liabilities = $631,880.98

Quick Ratio = ($9,891,156.92 - $343,000.00) / $631,880.98
Quick Ratio = $9,548,156.92 / $631,880.98
Quick Ratio = 15.11

## Calculating the Net Profit Margin

Net Profit Margin is calculated as:
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

From the income statement:
- Net Profit = $1,167,783.63
- Total Revenue = $3,397,619.40

Net Profit Margin = ($1,167,783.63 / $3,397,619.40) × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 0.3437 × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 34.37%
